That hotkey had not met the 10-round eligibility requirement yet at that round, so it was not eligible. This is clearly written in the main README under Weight Distribution here: https://github.com/minos-protocol/minos_subnet#weight-distribution

That said, as part of the (potential) tie-break rule hotfix I described earlier today , we are also reviewing whether the number of rounds required for eligibility should be adjusted.

@Centrum | Minos SN107 [ミ] 
i am not sure what to update as a miner.
do you currently recommend miners to update only config file?

We’ve flipped the switch and chromosome 22 is now part of the miners’ task pool.

For the next couple of days, we’ll keep the mix gradual: **60% chr21, 30% chr22, and 10% chr20**. This should make the transition smoother, avoid a sudden impact on miners, and give everyone time to adjust.

@zk [τ, τ] your configs may or may not carry over cleanly to the new chromosome. That’ll be part of the ongoing experiment. Most likely, the core of your config will still be useful, but not all of it will transfer directly, so some tuning will probably be needed.
